**Job Description****Company Profile: A. K Group, a financial conglomerate was founded by Mr. A.K Mittal with a vision to operate and develop the Indian debt capital markets which were in nascent stage. A. K Group over the period has emerged as one of the most trusted Bond Houses of India, aimed at providing the most competent solutions to its clients. Proficient at the Fixed Income market Segment of the Indian Economy, the group works towards its definitive motive of “A Bond in every hand”.**  

A. K Group offers varied range of financial products and services like Investment Banking, Broking & Distribution, Advisory Services, Financing and Structured Products.
Website: www.akgroup.co.in
Department: Credit
Designation: VP **Responsibilities –**
 Credit analysis of proposed investee companies in bfsi, infrastructure sector (power generation, power transmission, renewable energy (solar / wind), road or any other sectors.
 To understand and evaluate financial statements;
 Promoter and Corporate DD based on publicly available information;
 Reviewing transaction related agreements such as redevelopment agreements, contracts for infra companies, etc;
 To draft investment notes and credit notes / presentations;
 Need to evaluate debt investment opportunities in various instruments such as Security Receipts / Non-Convertible Debentures / Loans;
 Identification of risks involved in lending transaction and recommending proposed mitigants;
 Undertaking due diligence on proposed investee companies;
 Assistance in drafting of term sheets, reviewing investment related documents such as Facility Agreement / Debenture Trust Deed, Escrow Agreement, Guarantee Deed, Share Pledge agreement, etc;
 Monitoring of transactions post disbursement and till final repayment;
 Assisting in investment banking of transactions;
 Need to have good knowledge of relevant laws / regulations such as Companies Act, RERA, SARFAESI, IBC, etc
Education: Graduate/Post Graduate **Work Experience:** More than 6years
Desired Skills:
 Communication,
 Analysis
 good knowledge of Laws
